heels to support those systems. The official Python packaging guide provides documentation on [creating](https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/distributing-packages/#packaging-your-project) and [uploading](https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/distributing-packages/#upload-your-distributions) distributions.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/2", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/2/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/2/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/2/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/2", "id": 265273280, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyNjUyNzMyODA=", "number": 2, "title": "Glob pattern ignores are not working as expected", "user": {"login": "5j9", "id": 1055747, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwNTU3NDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1055747?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9", "html_url": "https://github.com/5j9", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/5j9/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-10-13T12:32:52Z", "updated_at": "2017-10-13T23:16:35Z", "closed_at": "2017-10-13T17:30:24Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "What is the expected output of running flake8 in the test directory? I'm getting\r\n\r\n```\r\na@D MINGW64 /d/flake8-per-file-ignores/test (master)\r\n$ flake8.exe\r\n.\\bar.py:1:1: D100 Missing docstring in public module\r\n.\\foo.py:0:1: X100 Superfluous per-file-ignores for E302,F401\r\n.\\subdir\\a\\foo_a.py:1:1: F821 undefined name 'x'\r\n.\\subdir\\a\\foo_a.py:1:1: D100 Missing docstring in public module\r\n.\\subdir\\b\\foo_b.py:1:1: D100 Missing docstring in public module\r\n.\\subdir\\b\\foo_b.py:1:6: E712 comparison to True should be 'if cond is True:' or 'if cond:'\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut according to the `setup.cfg` file I believe E712 and F821 should have been  ignored somehow. Am I missing something?\r\n", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/1", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/1/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/1/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/1/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/1", "id": 263743402, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyNjM3NDM0MDI=", "number": 1, "title": "Support globs", "user": {"login": "The-Compiler", "id": 625793, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYyNTc5Mw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/625793?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler", "html_url": "https://github.com/The-Compiler", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/The-Compiler/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2017-10-08T19:09:06Z", "updated_at": "2017-11-22T06:21:01Z", "closed_at": "2017-10-08T22:33:21Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hey, coming from flake8-putty, and this finally gives me hope to upgrade to flake8 3.0! \ud83c\udf89 \r\n\r\nHowever, I used to do this in flake8-putty, as I want to be more forgiving for docstrings in test files: `tests/*/test_*.py : +D100,D101,D401`\r\n\r\nIt'd be nice if I could do something like that with `flake8-per-file-ignores` too!", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}]}